Moulton Hires Julier for Renewable-Energy Fund, Telegraph Says

-- B y   S i m o n   C l a r k
-- 
2011-05-08T10:02:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-08/moulton-hires-julier-for-renewable-energy-fund-telegraph-says.html
Jon Moulton , founder of Better Capital
Plc, hired Vince Julier to co-manage Greensphere Capital, a U.K.
renewable-energy fund, the  Sunday Telegraph  reported, without
citing the source of the information.  Julier previously worked at London-based oil company BP
Plc, according to the report. At Greensphere he will work with
former Goldman Sachs Group Inc. banker Divya Seshamani. Moulton,
a veteran private-equity investor, will chair the 200 million-
pound ($327 million) fund, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Simon Clark in London at 
